= La columna quiere sangre

The message comes down the trail with the particular heat of young men who have won a few and want more: the Guerrero column has a cacique in its sights — a real one, the kind who burns ejidos and buys judges — and it wants permission to execute him. The case against the man is airtight and the case for restraint is strategic, which is to say it sounds, to twenty-year-olds with rifles, like cowardice wearing a necktie.

This is the war the party never had: not the enemy, but your own people, disciplined or not by a decision made far from the fire. Say yes and the column loves you and the reprisal comes; say no and you keep the strategy and lose a little of the thing that makes men climb mountains for you.

- @columna_autorizar: Authorize it. The cacique has earned it and the column needs to know the leadership trusts its judgment.
- @columna_frenar: Hold them. Explain the arithmetic — a dead cacique is a battalion in the sierra by Friday — and spend authority to enforce it.
- @columna_negociar: Neither: turn the energy sideways. Give the column a sanctioned operation instead — a target the strategy actually wants hit.

@columna_autorizar
go-to: post_event
on-arrival: moral_columnas += 8; sup_peasants += 3; represion += 5; expediente += 5; guar_guerrero += 6; memorial += 1

The cacique's reign ends in his own doorway, and for a week the Costa Grande breathes the specific air of a debt collected. The column would follow you into the sea now. So, unfortunately, would a battalion of paratroopers: the reprisal arrives on schedule, falling as it always falls not on the gunmen but on the villages, and the leadership adds one more entry to the ledger of victories that cost more than defeats.

@columna_frenar
go-to: post_event
choose-if: moral_columnas >= 55
unavailable-subtitle: Restraining a column that wants blood takes standing the leadership does not currently have with the fighters.
on-arrival: moral_columnas -= 6; unity += 3; inteligencia += 2; guar_guerrero -= 2

The order is obeyed, barely, and resented, fully. The cacique lives; the sweep that his death would have triggered does not come; the zone stays quiet and workable for another season. The column files the decision under the word it uses for all such decisions — *prudencia* — and pronounces it exactly the way the '68 students once pronounced it about the party. The wheel turns. You are the cautious ones now, and the young are learning to spit the word.

@columna_negociar
go-to: post_event
choose-if: parque >= 2
unavailable-subtitle: Redirecting the column's energy takes materiel for a real operation — 2 parque.
on-arrival: moral_columnas += 3; parque -= 2; guar_guerrero += 3; expediente += 3; guerrilla_meter += 2

You give the column what it actually needs, which is not the cacique but the feeling of forward motion: a sanctioned target the strategy wants hit anyway — a garrison payroll, an army radio — planned properly, resourced, blessed. The cacique keeps his skin and the column keeps its edge, and both are pointed where the leadership wants them pointed. It is the hardest trick in commanding fighters: to make discipline feel like permission.

@la_deriva
title: La deriva
